New York (CNN Business)A key measure of inflation rose 5.8% between December 2020 and December 2021, the Bureau of Economic Analysis reported Friday. It was the biggest advance since 1982. Energy prices alone rose nearly 30% over the course of 2021, while food prices climbed 5.7%. Stripping out those two components, the core consumer price index -- which is the Federal Reserve's preferred measure of inflation -- rose 4.9% in the 12 months to December. That was the fastest price hike by that measure since 1983. This is a developing story. It will be updated 